Date: Tue, 29 Oct 2003
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GideonOnline [edited]
<http://www.GideonOnline.net>

Some background on meningococcal disease in the Russian Federation
---------------------------------------------------
Large epidemics of serogroup A meningococcal disease occurred in Moscow in
1931 and 1940.
In 1968, a serogroup A epidemic was reported in Lipezk.
An outbreak of group A meningococcal meningitis (188 cases) was reported
from Moscow during Jan to Apr 1996 -- primarily affecting the Vietnamese
community [see ProMED refs. below]. As a result, hundreds of thousands of
Muscovites were immunized with A polysaccharide vaccine.
Year / meningococcal disease - cases / fatal cases
1966 / 491
1967 / 532
1968 / 656
1969 / 2120
1971 / 6716
1972 / 13 326
1973 / 21 353
